This paper is about evaluating natural language generation models, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The evaluation methods discussed in the paper involve measuring text similarity and distinguishing between human-written and machine-generated text, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
